 Voice Actress\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2020\n|6th Anime Trending Awards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://anitrendz.net/ata/2020/winners|title=Official Winners - 6th Anime Trending Awards|last=|first=|date=|website=Anime Trending|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 6, 2020}}</ref>\n|Best Voice Actress|Best Voice Actress\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://lineblog.me/aoi_yuki/ Official blog] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://profit-v.com/pro/talent_yuki.html Official agency profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{ann|people|68107|Aoi Y\u016bki}}\n* {{IMDb name|2976492}}\n\n{{Seiyu Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role}}\n{{Newtype Anime Award for Best Actress}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yuki, Aoi}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Japanese child actresses]]\n[[Category:Japanese female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese television personalities]]\n[[Category:Japanese video game actresses]]\n[[Category:Japanese voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Chiba Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Voice actresses from Chiba Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Waseda University alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese actress, voice actress and singer}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Aoi Y\u016bki\n| image              = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt                = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \u60a0\u6728 \u78a7\n| native_name_lang   = ja\n| birth_name         = Aoi Yabusaki<ref name=\"Megami Magazine 13 9 100\">Matsuo, K\u014d. Y\u016bki, Aoi. \"\u3042\u306e\u9803\u3001\u79c1\u305f\u3061\u3082\u80b2\u3061\u3056\u304b\u308a\u3067\u3057\u305f \u677e\u5c3e\u8861 \u60a0\u6728\u78a7 \u30b9\u30da\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u5bfe\u8ac7\". ''[[Megami Magazine]]''. [[Gakken]]. 13(9), 2011,  p. 100. {{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1992|03|27}}\n| birth_place        = [[Chiba Prefecture]], Japan\n| death_date         = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1992|03|27}} Death date then birth -->\n| death_place        = \n| education          = [[Waseda University]]<ref name=\"grad\">{{cite web | url=http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=303 | title=\u305d\u3064\u304e\u3087\u3046 | date=March 3, 2010 | accessdate=June 13, 2015 | author=Y\u016bki, Aoi | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150615064750/http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=303 | archive-date=June 15, 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"ugrad\">{{cite web | url=http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=686 | title=\u304a\u30fc\u304f\u307e\u3055\u3093\u3068\u3086\u304b\u3044\u306a\u306a\u304b\u307e\u305f\u3061 | date=March 26, 2014 | accessdate=June 13, 2015 | author=Y\u016bki, Aoi | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150615072258/http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=686 | archive-date=June 15, 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n*Actress\n*[[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]]\n*singer\n}}\n| years_active       = 1996\u2013present\n| agent              = [[Pro-Fit]]\n| height             = 145 cm<ref name=\"agency\"/>\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes   <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| background         = solo_singer  <!-- mandatory format: please do not change or remove -->\n| genre              = [[J-Pop]]\n| instrument         = Vocals\n| years_active       = 2012\u2013present\n| label              = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Victor Entertainment|FlyingDog]] (2012\u20132016)\n*[[Nippon Columbia]] (2017\u2013present)\n}}\n| associated_acts    = Petit Milady\n}}\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Aoi Yabusaki'''|\u516b\u6b66\u5d0e \u78a7|Yabusaki Aoi|born March 27, 1992}}, better known by her stage name {{Nihongo|'''Aoi Y\u016bki'''|\u60a0\u6728 \u78a7|Y\u016bki Aoi}}, is a Japanese actress, [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]] and singer represented by [[Pro-Fit]].<ref name=\"agency\">[http://profit-v.com/pro/talent_yuki.html Agency profile]</ref> She played the young Murasaki Kuh\u014din in ''[[Kure-nai]]''. She had two roles in 2008, eight in 2009 and twelve in 2010. She graduated from high school in March 2010 and university in March 2014.<ref name=\"grad\">{{cite web | url=http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=303 | title=\u305d\u3064\u304e\u3087\u3046 | date=March 3, 2010 | accessdate=June 13, 2015 | author=Y\u016bki, Aoi | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150615064750/http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=303 | archive-date=June 15, 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"ugrad\">{{cite web | url=http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=686 | title=\u304a\u30fc\u304f\u307e\u3055\u3093\u3068\u3086\u304b\u3044\u306a\u306a\u304b\u307e\u305f\u3061 | date=March 26, 2014 | accessdate=June 13, 2015 | author=Y\u016bki, Aoi | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150615072258/http://aoimania.com/blog/?id=686 | archive-date=June 15, 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{{TOC limit}}\n\n==Biography==\nY\u016bki was born in [[Chiba Prefecture]]. She entered the entertainment industry at the age of four.<ref name=\"studio\">{{cite news|title=Aoi Y\u016bki Bio|newspaper=[[Yomiuri Shimbun]]|date=December 13, 2008}}</ref> As a child, she acted in films and dramas. From 1999 to 2002, she made regular appearances on the variety shows ''Appare Sanma Dai-sensei'' and ''Yappari Sanma Dai-sensei'' which aired on [[Fuji Television|Fuji TV]]. When she was in fifth grade, she made her debut as a voice actress.<ref name=\"studio\"/>\n\nIn late 2006, she was affiliated with the theater company Central.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2007-12-17|url=http://blue.ap.teacup.com/applet/aoilogic/archive?b=38|title=\u300c\u7dca\u6025\uff01\u544a\u77e5\u266a\u300d\u3000\u3000\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|author=Y\u016bki, Aoi|publisher=i|accessdate=March 8, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150410115137/http://blue.ap.teacup.com/applet/aoilogic/archive?b=38|archive-date=April 10, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> After her admission to high school in August 2007, she joined the agency Breath, changing her [[stage name]] to Aoi Y\u016bki. She got her first major role in 2008 in ''[[Kure-nai]]''<ref name=kurenai>{{cite web|title=Staff & Cast|url=http://www.samidareso.com/staff.html|publisher=[[Brains Base]]|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref> as Murasaki Kuh\u014din. In August of the same year, she moved to the agency Pro-Fit. In 2009, she starred in two anime: ''[[Anyamaru Tantei Kiruminzuu]]'' as Mikogami Riko<ref name=\"atk\">{{cite web|title=\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u6771\u4eac\u30fb\u3042\u306b\u3066\u308c\u3000\u3042\u306b\u3083\u307e\u308b\u63a2\u5075\u30ad\u30eb\u30df\u30f3\u305a\u3045|url=http://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/kirumin/|publisher=[[TV Tokyo]]|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref> and ''[[Yumeiro Patissiere]]'' as Amano Ichigo,<ref name=yp>{{cite web|title=Yumeiro Patissiere Ichigo profile|url=http://www.ytv.co.jp/yumepati_pc/chara/ichigo.html|publisher=[[Yomiuri Telecasting Corporation]]|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref> respectively. After that, she voiced the female protagonists of several of her series, notably [[List of Pok\u00e9mon characters#Unova Gym Leaders|Iris]] from ''[[Pok\u00e9mon (anime)|Pok\u00e9mon: Best Wishes!]]''<ref name=pokemon-bw>{{cite web|title=\u30dd\u30b1\u30c3\u30c8\u30e2\u30f3\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc \u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u30a6\u30a4\u30c3\u30b7\u30e5 \u30b7\u30fc\u30ba\u30f32 \u30c7\u30b3\u30ed\u30e9\u30a2\u30c9\u30d9\u30f3\u30c1\u30e3\u30fc\uff1a\u3042\u306b\u3066\u308c\uff1a\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u6771\u4eac|url=http://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/anime/pokemon_bw/staff/|publisher=[[TV Tokyo]]|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref> and Victorique de Blois from ''[[Gosick]]''.<ref name=gosick>{{cite web|title=Staff & Cast|url=http://www.gosick.tv/staff_cast/index.html|publisher=GOSICK Production Committee|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Y\u016bki voiced [[Madoka Kaname]] in ''[[Puella Magi Madoka Magica]]''.<ref name=madoka-magica>{{cite web|title=Puella Magi Madoka Magica's Voice Samples Posted|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2010-11-04/puella-magi-madoka-magica-voice-samples-posted|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=July 23, 2014|date=November 4, 2011}}</ref> In October of the same year, she won the award for best voice actor in the Newtype x Machi Asobi Anime Awards. She was awarded the Best Lead Actress Award in the 6th [[Seiyu Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|title=6th Annual Seiy\u016b Award Winners Announced|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-03-01/6th-annual-seiyu-awards-winners-announced|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=March 8, 2013}}</ref> In 2013, Y\u016bki and [[Ayana Taketatsu]], formed the singing unit Petit Milady.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2013-03-22/aoi-yuki-and-ayana-taketatsu-form-petit-milady-singing-unit|title=Aoi Yuki & Ayana Taketatsu Form petit milady Singing Unit|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=March 22, 2013}}</ref> Together, they performed the song {{nihongo|\"Kagami no Dual-ism\"|\u93e1\u306e\u30c7\u30e5\u30a2\u30eb\u30fb\u30a4\u30ba\u30e0|The Mirror of Dual-ism}}, which was used as the third opening theme to the 2013 anime television series ''[[List of Yu-Gi-Oh! Zexal II episodes|Yu-Gi-Oh! Zexal II]]'', and in 2014, performed the song \"Azurite\", which was used as the opening theme for the 2014 anime series ''[[The Pilot's Love Song]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Toaru Hik\u016bshi e no Koiuta Anime's Promo Features Opening Theme by petit milady|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-12-19/toaru-hikushi-e-no-koiuta-anime-promo-features-opening-theme-by-petit-milady|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=July 23, 2014}}</ref> She has also played Hibiki Tachibana in ''[[Symphogear]]'',<ref name=\"vadb\"/> Yuuki Konno in ''[[Sword Art Online|Sword Art Online II]]'', Tanya Degurechaff in ''[[The Saga of Tanya the Evil]]'', Yoshiko Hanabatake in ''[[Aho-Girl]]'',<ref name=\"vadb\">{{cite web|title=\u60a0\u6728\u78a7(Aoi Yuuki)\uff1d\u516b\u6b66\u5d0e\u78a7|url=http://gph.sakura.ne.jp/va_memo/system/vadb.cgi?action=view_ind&value=01552&namecode=7|website=Voice Artist DataBase|publisher=GamePlaza Haruka|accessdate=March 27, 2018|language=Japanese}}</ref> Nodoka Hanadera/Cure Grace in ''[[Healin' Good PreCure]]'', Sonya in ''[[Fairy Tail]]'' and Futaba Sakura in ''[[Persona 5]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television animation===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Kino's Journey]]'' || Sakura<ref name=\"vadb\"/>\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Aishiteruze Baby]]'' || Marika<ref name=\"vadb\"/>\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[Onegai My Melody]]'' || Koto Yumeno<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Onegai My Melody|Onegai My Melody: Kuru Kuru Shuffle]]'' || Koto Yumeno \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Onegai My Melody|Onegai My Melody: Sukkiri]]'' || Koto Yumeno \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2008 || ''[[Kure-nai]]'' || Murasaki Kuh\u014din<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Corpse Princess|Shikabane Hime: Aka]]'' || Akira T\u014doka<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" | 2009 || ''[[Akikan!]]'' || Budoko <ref name=\"vadb\"/>\n|-\n|''[[Anyamaru Tantei Kiruminzuu]]'' || Riko Mikogami<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Nogizaka Haruka no Himitsu|Nogizaka Haruka no Himitsu: Purezza]]'' || Hikari Hatsuse<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Corpse Princess|Shikabane Hime: Kuro]]'' || Akira T\u014doka \n|-\n|''[[Sora no Manimani]]'' || Maibara<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Yumeiro Patissiere]]'' || Ichigo Amano<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''Yutori-chan'' || Yutori Tanaka \n|-\n| rowspan=\"11\" | 2010 || ''[[Dance in the Vampire Bund]]'' || Mina Tepes<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Durarara!!]]'' || Shinra Kishitani (young) \n|-\n|''[[Hyakka Ry\u014dran Samurai Girls]]'' || J\u016bbei Yagy\u016b<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Ichiban Ushiro no Dai Ma\u014d]]'' || Korone<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n|-\n|''[[Jewelpet|Jewelpet Tinkle]]'' || Amelie<ref name=\"vadb\"/> \n